      "side": 1,
      "message": "Ha! I began work on this patch before unformat_base10() was merged and I did not notice it.\n\nOn a more serious note: 1) unformat_base10() parses a signed value (despite its return type), and when we parse bitrates, we want an unsigned value. Maybe we should have signed and unsigned versions of unformat_base10?\n\n2) Currently both unformat_base10 and the proposed unformat_bitrate return uword, which, on a 32-bit cpu, is too small for \u0027tera\u0027 and practically too small for \u0027giga\u0027. I propose that unformat_base10 should return type \u0027i64\u0027 and whatever unsigned version should return \u0027u64\u0027 since that reflects the demands of the parsed values. Do you agree?",
      "parentUuid": "1dfc66df_d0a72b42",
